or
or
URL is converted as described in the string conversion. All different forms are equivalent; the name of the used attribute has no influence on the data source type. It is thus perfectly legal to write . Two other attributes allow to control finely the data source:
charset: specifies the character encoding of the data ("UTF-8" by default);
encoding: same as above;
